HEADWORD: magnetron
<hw>mag"ne*tron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>a diode vacuum
tube in which the flow of electrons from a central cathode to a
cylindrical anode is controlled by crossed magnetic and electric fields;
used mainly in microwave oscillators.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magnifiable</ent>⟦br⟧
